---------------------- To Run ----------------------
stripe listen --forward-to localhost:3000/api/stripe_hook

/root npm run dev

---------------------- Directory structure ----------------------


---------------------- To deploy contracts ----------------------
go to ./ethereum and run 
node compile.js to get new build files
node deploy.js to get new contract factory address

copy address to factory.js

---------------------- Eth contract address ----------------------
/backend/ethBackend.js
/backend/ethOpenVerification.js
/ethereum/verification.js
/pages/api/create-verification-session.js

---------------------- Functionality ----------------------
successful id verifications will lead to hash being submitted to contract
contract is linked with zk verifier contract and so has one function (verifyHash) that should be called once the client has 
generated their zkp, this should return a bool about whether the transaction has been successful
(this has working functionality but no database or error handling)
